NAME
<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>            shutdown - shut down system/emulator

SYNOPSIS
<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>            shutdown -h

<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>            shutdown -r

DESCRIPTION
<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>            Shutdown halts (-h) or restarts (-r) <action name=emu(1)>emu(1)</action> or a native
<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>            kernel. If restarted, <action name=emu(1)>emu(1)</action> will be given the same options
<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>            as were given it when it started.

FILES
<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>            /dev/sysctl

SOURCE
<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>            /dis/shutdown  <action name=sh(1)>sh(1)</action> script
SEE ALSO
